\begin_layout Standard
Lethal samples can be incorporated into both IMR and CKMR analyses.
 In this study,
 we considered lethal samples as a potential replacement for some live samples.
 Partial substitution of lethal samples for non-lethal (biopsy) samples resulted in similar precision on abundance estimates.
 In previous years,
 50 samples per year were collected from harvested animals by the FWS WHMP.
 However,
 the total harvest in Alaska is estimated to number ~4,210 walruses per year 
