 followed this approach for school shark,
 using (substantially inaccurate) vertebral ages rather than epigenetic clocks.
 In the case of ICKMR,
 the information from recaptured individuals will also be helpful in resolving ages,
 since the interval between sampling will be known.
 Nevertheless,
 in severe cases uncertainty about age can drastically limit the ability to gain information from CKMR,
 even when the number of kin-pairs found is high and the model is adjusted properly,
 as noted from practical experience by 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
